# {{CMD_PREFIX}}-upgrade

Model/effort: Sonnet / high.

The down-sync. Pulls approved framework improvements from the hub into this brain without
disturbing project-owned work. Follows the propagation contract; lands via PR.

## Steps
1. OPEN-lite: read the operating contract §7 and the propagation contract; state the upgrade
   objective.
2. Preview (dry-run): run the down-sync engine through the adapter seam —
   `run.sh upgrade-brain --brain <this brain>` (the `upgrade-brain` task; no `--apply`). It
   resolves the gap and, if behind, prints the planned core refresh, the manual-review modules
   (`adopted: false`), and any extension conflicts. If it reports "up to date", stop.
3. Review the plan: confirm every planned write is core-layer and that no `extensions` path
   appears under conflicts. Handle manual-review modules by hand — never overwrite them.
4. Apply: re-run with `--apply` (add `--force` only to repair drift at the same version). The
   engine refreshes the enabled core modules, bumps each `synced_from` and the manifest
   `framework_version = latest`, and records the upgrade under `05-logs/upgrades/`; extensions
   are never touched.
5. CLOSE ritual: regenerate the capabilities map; run the test suite the way the project runs
   it; open the change as a PR and push (the PR is the control gate).

## Done when
The manifest is at the latest framework version, core deltas are applied with extensions
intact, and the upgrade is in a PR with validation evidence.
